Java.Simple GUI:
# Create a simple GUI in Java  

```
package yourPackage;  

//We run it with Java Swing  
import javax.swing.JFrame;

//We create a class named GuiExample which extends JFrame  

public class GuiExample extends JFrame {  
    public GuiExample(){  
        //sets the size of the frame  
        setSize(800,600);  

        //puts frame in middle of frame  
        setLocationRelativeTo(null);  

        //sets visibility true  
        setVisible(true);  
    }  

    //We need to run it  
    public static void main(String[] args) {  
        new GuiExample();  
    }  
}
```

Java.Layouts:
# Borderlayout

## Create a BorderLayout

![](https://imgur.com/prBLVz4)  
These are the Positions in the layout

```
BorderLayout bl = new BorderLayout();  
frame.setLayout(bl);

or:  frame.setLayout(new BorderLayout());  
```
## Add something to your frame within a Borderlayout   (ex: JPanel)
```
JPanel panel = new JPanel();  
frame.add(panel, BorderLayout.CENTER);  
//This will add the panel in center of the frame.
```

